&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Don&#39;t see a position that fits your background?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;No worries!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;If you have a passion for gaming and want to help us, bring joy to others one game at a time, fill out the general application below and tell us a little bit about yourself. Our friendly recruiters are standing by and will get in touch when we have an opportunity that fits your background and skills.&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;117&quot; data-end=&quot;289&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;117&quot; data-end=&quot;168&quot;&gt;MobilityWare is NOW looking for a Game Designer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team and work on our vast portfolio of casual mobile games that bring joy to millions of gamers worldwide!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;291&quot; data-end=&quot;712&quot;&gt;This position will be a &lt;strong data-start=&quot;315&quot; data-end=&quot;345&quot;&gt;key member of a small team&lt;/strong&gt; in a start-up-like environment at our growing studio. You will be responsible for creating &lt;strong data-start=&quot;437&quot; data-end=&quot;462&quot;&gt;Game Design Documents&lt;/strong&gt; that empower Engineers, Artists, and QA to excel in their roles. You’ll also work directly in &lt;strong data-start=&quot;557&quot; data-end=&quot;566&quot;&gt;Unity&lt;/strong&gt; to generate content and refine gameplay experiences, all while focusing on delighting our players and bringing new ideas to life with the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;714&quot; data-end=&quot;783&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;714&quot; data-end=&quot;748&quot;&gt;We offer relocation assistance&lt;/strong&gt; to help make your move seamless.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;785&quot; data-end=&quot;862&quot;&gt;If you have a passion for gaming and want to make an impact, &lt;strong data-start=&quot;846&quot; data-end=&quot;860&quot;&gt;apply now!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable Engineers, Artists and QA through the creation of thoughtful, implementation-focused Game and Feature Design Documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using Unity and in-house tools to create design game content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data to understand our customers and create, tune, and balance features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a generalist game designer, ready to work end-to-end, from core loop development to live service management on new games and features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seek out critiques and opportunities to improve; iterate without attachment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become an industry expert on casual mobile game design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a team player who listens to, encourages, and supports others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of professional experience contributing to the design of casual or mobile games, either in a studio role or live production environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine passion for casual mobile games, with an understanding of what keeps players engaged over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to write clear and structured Game Design Documents (GDDs) and iterate on them in collaboration with a cross-discipline development team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating wireframes, mock-ups, technical flows, and research materials to support early concepting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with using data and player feedback to evaluate features and inform design decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to a range of design responsibilities, such as level design, economy tuning, feature planning, or QA/test documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A growth mindset and willingness to take on new challenges, absorb feedback, and develop new skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, respectful attitude with a desire to contribute to a positive and supportive team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiasm for joining a small, fast-moving team where adaptability and curiosity are key to success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;A Little Bit About Us:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/

&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 14pt; margin-bottom: 5pt; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work across MobilityWare&#39;s portfolio of beloved mobile games, supporting titles enjoyed by millions of players around the world. As a Product Manager, you&#39;ll help drive the development of our flagship card games while gaining hands-on experience across the full product development lifecycle. You&#39;ll contribute to product strategy and roadmap planning, leverage data to inform decisions, and develop deep expertise in the competitive mobile gaming landscape.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 14pt; margin-bottom: 5pt; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The ideal candidate is curious, data-driven, and passionate about mobile games. You thrive in a collaborative environment, take ownership of your work and professional growth, and are motivated to create player-first experiences informed by data, player feedback, and market insights.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 14pt; margin-bottom: 5pt; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Support Product Owners in sprint reviews, planning, and design backlog, and agile workflows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Develop a deep understanding of player mindset and motivations and learn to connect design thinking to key performance indicators, business value, and feature success metrics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Contribute to future roadmap ideation by tracking feature status, documenting Expected Outcomes tied to KPIs, and synthesizing player and stakeholder feedback.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Lead comprehensive market and competitive research across the casual mobile gaming landscape, identifying trends and player behavior patterns that inform product decisions and roadmap priorities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Partner with the Data Analytics team to develop A/B test ideas, define success metrics and KPIs, and begin interpreting test results with guidance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Support feature design and specification by applying player insight and business goal alignment to product requirements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Prepare and deliver internal presentations with clear data and insights, building confidence in communicating ideas across teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Build strong cross functional relationships with Design, Engineering, and Analytics to support feature delivery and milestone planning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: helvetica

&lt;p&gt;This is a rare opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An impactful position at a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;profitable, stable, self-funded studio with one of the best no-crunch cultures in our industry&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;And you? You’re an architect of joy. A &lt;strong&gt;tech artist&lt;/strong&gt; who wears many hats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Particle systems, prefabs, shaders. You build interfaces. Shape visual effects.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Make Unity sing&lt;/strong&gt;. You use timing, movement, and energetic animations to bring excitement to players.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You construct juicy, delightful experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re organized and creative.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;A master collaborator&lt;/strong&gt; who derives joy from helping your peers in art, design, and engineering. You’re excited by the idea of iterating quickly on a portfolio of 30+ games.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If that resonates, then we need your help&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;bringing joy to others, one game at a time&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be an amazing tech artist, &lt;/strong&gt;bridging the gap between art and engineering, creating tools to streamline the pipeline, and optimizing visual assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bring art mockups to life inside Unity&lt;/strong&gt;, including all aspects: particle systems, shaders, VFX, prefab/UI creation, and building amazing animations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with timeliness, quality, and adaptability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate effectively&lt;/strong&gt; in a dynamic, fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communicate&lt;/strong&gt; timelines, own tasks, and contribute to successful sprints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Embrace using AI&lt;/strong&gt; to achieve “more, better, faster”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relate to our motto: “&lt;strong&gt;Slow Down to Speed Up&lt;/strong&gt;”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications for Position:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B.S. in a relevant field&lt;/strong&gt; (or equivalent studio experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5+ years of professional game dev&lt;/strong&gt; (mobile experience is &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expertise in the Unity editor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;standard art tools (ex&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Photoshop, Illustrator, Figma, …)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A growth mindset&lt;/strong&gt; that embraces continuous learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passion for evergreen games&lt;/strong&gt; that reach tens of millions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Little Bit About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most studios would be grateful to have even one game in Apple Arcade’s top twenty. We have four, making us one of the top mobile studios in the world. With our headquarters in the heart of Orange County and a growing studio in Utah, we’re dedicated to our mission of bringing joy to others one game at a time. Ever since our flagship title Solitaire hit the Apple App Store on the day it opened in 2008, MobilityWare has been entertaining gamers around the world. With a product portfolio that includes beloved hits such as FreeCell, Spider, Spades, Hearts, Mahjong, Yatzy, Splash Sort, and Bubble Shooter Pop, our games have been downloaded over 600 MILLION times.&lt;/p&gt;
